/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4727:\"<p>It is with great pleasure that we announce the merger of <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">Slightly Modified Options Framework (SMOF)</a> and Redux Framework!  The Redux Team is proud to welcome Syamil MJ (<a href=\"http://github.com/syamilmj\">@syamilmj</a>), creator of <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> to our family.  We can’t wait to see what he brings to the table.  There’s no denying the fantastic work he’s done with <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a>.  Historically, <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> has been the foundation for countless themes on ThemeForest and across the net, so we can’t wait to see what Syamil will bring to the table.  Welcome to the family <a href=\"http://github.com/syamilmj\">Syamil</a>!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">Slightly Modified Options Framework (SMOF)</a> History</h3>\n<p>On September 29th, 2011, Syamil introduced <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> to the world . Based heavily on <a href=\"https://github.com/helgatheviking\">helgatheviking</a>’s KIA Options Framework, (which was forked from the original <a href=\"https://github.com/devinsays/options-framework-plugin\">Options Framework</a>) by <a href=\"https://github.com/devinsays/\">Devin Price</a>, many additional ideals and asthetic improvement came from <a href=\"https://github.com/valendesigns/option-tree\">Options Tree</a>.  <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF’s</a> goal became one of offering a modern-looking, feature-rich options framework many theme developers adopted.   It became a solid example of what quality work does for the community.</p>\n<h3>Dovy Paukstys: I Never Dared to Dream…</h3>\n<p>In July of 2013, I began contributing frequently to the <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> project.  I fixed bugs, changed things around, and created a fully integrated customizer experience.  However, I soon discovered I needed more.  Not because of <a href=\"http://github.com/syamilmj\">@syamilmj</a>‘s work, but because of the foundation in which <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> derived from.  I also discovered  <a href=\"https://github.com/leemason/NHP-Theme-Options-Framework\">NHP</a>.  I loved <a href=\"https://github.com/leemason/NHP-Theme-Options-Framework\">NHP</a>’s code, but it wasn’t as visually appealing as <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a>, by any means.  I created a fork of both, which I called <a href=\"https://github.com/SimpleRain/SimpleOptions\">SimpleOptions</a>.  After 3 months or so of work to merge the two frameworks, <a href=\"https://github.com/ghost1227\">@ghost1227</a> approached me with an offer I couldn’t refuse.  We realized it would benefit the community immensly if we joined forces instead of working apart.  Thus, Redux Framework 3.0 was born from the code of <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leemason/NHP-Theme-Options-Framework\">NHP</a>, and <a href=\"https://github.com/SimpleRain/SimpleOptions\">SimpleOptions</a>.  When I set out to work on <a href=\"https://github.com/SimpleRain/SimpleOptions\">SimpleOptions</a>, and later Redux, I never imagined that both the original creators of <a href=\"https://github.com/leemason/NHP-Theme-Options-Framework\">NHP</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> would join team Redux, birthing one of the most versitile WordPress options framework ever seen.  I am both honored and excited by the possibilities of our colaborated efforts.</p>\n<h2>To all <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> Users</h2>\n<p>Don’t worry, you’re not shut out in the cold!  We want to help you migrate seamlessly from <a href=\"https://github.com/syamilmj/Options-Framework\">SMOF</a> to Redux.  We’re pleased to announce the release of our <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/redux-converter/\">Redux Converter</a> tool, available at: http://wordpress.org/plugins/redux-converter/.   With this tool, you can test Redux immediately, generating a new config file on the fly based on your current SMOF config.  We also automate the data migration on theme activation (or upgrade) for you, providing peace of mind for you and your users.  Give it a try, we promise you’ll not be disappointed!</p>\n<h4>To infinity, and beyond…</h4>\n<p>There are so many amazing features in the works for Redux, and we want you to join us in the experience!  Hold on to your hats ladies and gentlemen, 2014 is going to be an amazing year!</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://reduxframework.com/2014/01/smof-merges-with-redux/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:31:\"http://reduxframework.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0: